\begin{aligned}
y^{\prime \prime} & =-\frac{4}{x} y^{\prime}-\frac{2}{x^2} y+\frac{2 \ln x}{x^2}, \quad 1 \leq x \leq 2 \\
y(1) & =\frac{1}{2}, \quad y(2)=\ln 2
\end{aligned}
\] Solusi eksak: \[
y(x)=\frac{4}{x}-\frac{2}{x^2}+\ln x-\frac{3}{2}
\]
